00:44:15,872 --> 00:44:18,172
I've never seen this before.

585
00:44:19,042 --> 00:44:22,082
Oh, right. Yoon Ji Na must've left it here...

586
00:44:22,082 --> 00:44:25,882
when she was in a rush to get to "Top 10 Songs" on time.

587
00:44:30,021 --> 00:44:32,151
What about this glass?

588
00:44:32,151 --> 00:44:34,522
Who else used this?

589
00:44:35,262 --> 00:44:37,862
How would I remember everyone who's used it?

590
00:44:42,631 --> 00:44:47,142
So why did you make me come all the way to Incheon?

591
00:44:56,151 --> 00:44:59,922
You already know what kind of upbringing I had.

592
00:44:59,922 --> 00:45:02,022
This was like my playground.

593
00:45:02,022 --> 00:45:05,951
I've played with it plenty of times, so I don't need it anymore.

594
00:45:06,662 --> 00:45:10,531
What do you say? Would you accept it?

595
00:45:10,531 --> 00:45:16,362
I've officially joined the company, and I feel that I can start afresh with you.

596
00:45:38,691 --> 00:45:45,821
So you're not photogenic, and you're a terrible actor.

597
00:45:47,202 --> 00:45:48,971
You're Soonyang's third-generation heir.

598
00:45:48,971 --> 00:45:52,842
You can easily buy yourself another playground like this.

599
00:45:52,842 --> 00:45:58,602
Did you actually think you could deceive me like this?

600
00:46:00,312 --> 00:46:06,181
If you want to marry me, it can't be because of me.

601
00:46:06,181 --> 00:46:10,791
I bet it's because of your grandpa, Chairman Jin Yang Cheol.

602
00:46:15,322 --> 00:46:17,532
What's wrong with that?

603
00:46:17,532 --> 00:46:20,862
I must do my very best to win my grandfather over.

604
00:46:20,862 --> 00:46:26,431
A devoted husband, model father, and successful businessman.

605
00:46:26,431 --> 00:46:29,791
I thought that was the kind of married life you wanted.

606
00:46:31,841 --> 00:46:34,581
What more do you need? Tell me.

607
00:46:36,111 --> 00:46:40,522
You hardly know me.

608
00:46:42,392 --> 00:46:47,892
If we knew everything about each other, we wouldn't want to get married.

609
00:46:49,492 --> 00:46:52,831
You, Ms. Mo Hyeon Min, intrigue me.

610
00:46:59,501 --> 00:47:04,912
If we wanted to land the New Seoul Town project,

611
00:47:04,912 --> 00:47:09,512
we'd have to see eye to eye with the next mayor of Seoul.

612
00:47:11,211 --> 00:47:13,281
When does the nomination period begin?

613
00:47:13,281 --> 00:47:18,222
The floor leaders of the leading and opposition parties are waiting for your call, sir.

614
00:47:18,222 --> 00:47:21,041
Is it not my money they're waiting for?

615
00:47:22,031 --> 00:47:24,131
They wouldn't give the project to a different company

616
00:47:24,131 --> 00:47:26,832
after getting your money for their campaign, right?

617
00:47:26,832 --> 00:47:31,702
Do you know why you must be careful when you spend someone else's money?

618
00:47:32,242 --> 00:47:36,042
The money I gave them isn't why they must listen to me.

619
00:47:36,042 --> 00:47:38,412
They have no choice but to do as I say

620
00:47:38,412 --> 00:47:42,151
because I have leverage over them since they received money from me.

621
00:47:42,151 --> 00:47:45,051
So it's a stick and not a carrot, after all.

622
00:47:48,352 --> 00:47:50,992
Choose one.

623
00:47:52,191 --> 00:47:55,592
Who has the look of the next mayor of Seoul?

624
00:48:06,441 --> 00:48:10,171
Oh! Prosecutor Choi Chang Je, right?

625
00:48:10,171 --> 00:48:12,182
- Who are you? 
 - What a coincidence!

626
00:48:12,182 --> 00:48:15,581
I really wanted to meet you. Who knew I'd run into you here?

627
00:48:23,651 --> 00:48:26,901
You know about Mayor Giuliani of New York, right?

628
00:48:26,901 --> 00:48:29,432
He was a prosecutor who came from nothing.

629
00:48:29,432 --> 00:48:31,961
Thanks to him, who fought against corruption,

630
00:48:31,961 --> 00:48:34,931
New York was reborn as a top city in the world.

631
00:48:34,931 --> 00:48:40,832
Just like New York has Giuliani, Seoul needs Mayor Choi Chang Je.

632
00:48:44,272 --> 00:48:48,842
A young, competent mayor who is perfect for Seoul.

633
00:48:49,512 --> 00:48:52,421
You're definitely not from the political circle.

634
00:48:52,421 --> 00:48:53,921
Oh...

635
00:48:54,722 --> 00:48:59,222
I'm Oh Se Hyeon from Miracle Investment.

636
00:49:00,892 --> 00:49:05,291
I'd like to sponsor your campaign, Mr. Choi.

637
00:49:06,431 --> 00:49:09,181
   

638
00:49:10,072 --> 00:49:11,931
"Miracle?"

639
00:49:16,542 --> 00:49:19,372
We cannot accept Miracle's support.

640
00:49:19,372 --> 00:49:25,181
Besides, you want the New Seoul Town project, which Soonyang Construction is after?

641
00:49:25,181 --> 00:49:31,721
CEO Oh, this is like declaring war on my father, Chairman Jin Yang Cheol.

642
00:49:32,592 --> 00:49:37,392
Never in my life have I seen anyone win against him.

643
00:49:37,392 --> 00:49:41,761
All will be fine if Chairman Jin never finds out about this.

644
00:49:41,761 --> 00:49:43,702
Am I wrong?

645
00:49:46,001 --> 00:49:50,802
I plan to take this to my grave.

646
00:49:50,802 --> 00:49:53,912
   

647
00:50:07,522 --> 00:50:09,992
So we're perfect partners now,

648
00:50:09,992 --> 00:50:12,691
since we share a secret.

649
00:50:14,102 --> 00:50:18,231
Then we must add on a little extra as hazard pay.

650
00:50:20,602 --> 00:50:25,212
As for the amount, instead of 10 billion won  ($10M) , make it 20 billion won  ($20M) .

651
00:50:27,512 --> 00:50:31,512
You sure take after your father.

652
00:50:33,422 --> 00:50:40,551
But the thing is, will the party nominate me?

653
00:50:40,551 --> 00:50:43,892
Those at Cheongwadae are tight,

654
00:50:43,892 --> 00:50:45,291
and people should know you

655
00:50:45,291 --> 00:50:47,461
if you want the spotlight at the confirmation hearing,

656
00:50:47,461 --> 00:50:48,362
but I'm...

657
00:50:48,362 --> 00:50:52,212
You reflect the spirit of the times, Prosecutor Choi.

658
00:50:52,212 --> 00:50:54,671
It's a quality that a politician absolutely needs.

659
00:50:54,671 --> 00:50:57,912
The spirit of the times...

660
00:50:58,671 --> 00:51:00,311
I do?

661
00:51:01,341 --> 00:51:03,011
- Yes! 
 - Yes?

662
00:51:03,011 --> 00:51:04,711
Yes!

663
00:51:11,921 --> 00:51:14,662
While investigating the family of Jea Construction's owner

664
00:51:14,662 --> 00:51:16,892
for dereliction of duty and embezzlement,

665
00:51:16,892 --> 00:51:18,631
the Seoul District Public Prosecutors' Office

666
00:51:18,631 --> 00:51:22,161
 confirmed that CEO Kang Man Soo illegally siphoned off 36 billion won  ($36M)  overseas. 

667
00:51:22,161 --> 00:51:24,332
 We've also requested an arrest warrant for Kim Jong Bok, 

668
00:51:24,332 --> 00:51:26,242
 the Commissioner of the Korea Customs Service, 

669
00:51:26,242 --> 00:51:28,642
 for deliberately concealing this. 

670
00:51:28,642 --> 00:51:31,272
This is clearly a corruption case caused by abuse of power.

671
00:51:31,272 --> 00:51:34,481
We, at the Prosecution Service, promise not to give in to any kind of external pressure

672
00:51:34,481 --> 00:51:39,181
and investigate the case until the end.

673
00:51:39,181 --> 00:51:40,282
That'd be all.

674
00:51:40,282 --> 00:51:43,151
   

675
00:51:43,151 --> 00:51:44,992
Prosecutor Choi! While you are investigating an incumbent minister,

676
00:51:44,992 --> 00:51:46,591
wasn't there any external pressure?

677
00:51:46,591 --> 00:51:49,332
You also investigated the cases involving Ahjin and Hando Steel.

678
00:51:49,332 --> 00:51:51,762
You're a member of the Soonyang family. Did anyone try to bribe you?

679
00:51:51,762 --> 00:51:54,331
Is there a reason you mainly handle corporate crime cases?

680
00:51:54,331 --> 00:51:55,832
Have you experienced any external pressure?

681
00:51:55,832 --> 00:51:57,531
- Just a comment, please! 
 - Say a few words!

682
00:51:57,531 --> 00:51:59,831
The spirit of the times?

683
00:51:59,831 --> 00:52:04,042
Since the financial crisis, everyone's been talking about sharing the pain.

684
00:52:04,811 --> 00:52:08,142
But they aren't the ones who caused this pain.

685
00:52:10,151 --> 00:52:14,052
Why are the powerless citizens the only ones suffering?

686
00:52:14,881 --> 00:52:21,852
Why is it that the powerless citizens are the only ones suffering?

687
00:52:22,791 --> 00:52:27,392
That is not justice.

688
00:52:29,672 --> 00:52:32,472
   

689
00:52:33,242 --> 00:52:35,271
   

