00:52:43,981 --> 00:52:47,352
All the shares that once belonged to CEO Kang Man Soo and his family

693
00:52:47,352 --> 00:52:50,122
got absorbed back to the company.

694
00:52:50,122 --> 00:52:54,351
We've become the major shareholder with just five percent of the shares.

695
00:52:54,351 --> 00:52:57,431
This also means we can participate in the New Seoul Town project.

696
00:52:57,431 --> 00:53:01,401
Hold on. Did we use Choi Chang Je to get Jea Construction?

697
00:53:01,401 --> 00:53:04,772
Or did we use Jea Construction to catapult Choi Chang Je to fame?

698
00:53:04,772 --> 00:53:08,401
What matters is that we already have Jea in the palm of our hand.

699
00:53:08,401 --> 00:53:14,112
And soon, we will also own the mayor of Seoul.

700
00:53:16,452 --> 00:53:19,452
 Choi Chang Je from the Seoul District Public Prosecutors' Office, 

701
00:53:19,452 --> 00:53:23,251
who has received strong support in pre-mayoral election polls,

702
00:53:23,251 --> 00:53:25,622
has announced that he was embarking on a political career.

703
00:53:25,622 --> 00:53:29,062
All eyes are on whether or not this son-in-law

704
00:53:29,062 --> 00:53:33,462
 of the Soonyang Group family will be nominated as a mayoral candidate. 

705
00:53:33,462 --> 00:53:38,832
 I will stand with my fellow citizens, with my fellow citizens of Seoul. 

706
00:53:46,441 --> 00:53:51,351
Those in the ruling party are supporting the other two candidates.

707
00:53:51,351 --> 00:53:53,122
What do you think, Do Jun?

708
00:53:53,122 --> 00:53:56,122
Who do you think is behind Uncle Chang Je?

709
00:53:56,122 --> 00:53:57,821
I'm not sure.

710
00:53:57,821 --> 00:54:00,922
I have no interest in politics.

711
00:54:00,922 --> 00:54:05,162
Grandfather will soon find out whom he's up against.

712
00:54:05,162 --> 00:54:07,401
He won't let them have their way.

713
00:54:07,401 --> 00:54:09,931
Uncle Chang Je and those in politics.

714
00:54:09,931 --> 00:54:13,101
   

715
00:54:16,012 --> 00:54:19,162
Mr. Kim Seong Hwan from the ruling party is on the phone.

716
00:54:22,981 --> 00:54:25,482
Hello. It's me, Jin Yang Cheol.

717
00:54:25,482 --> 00:54:28,251
Yes, Chairman. Right. 
    

718
00:54:28,251 --> 00:54:30,251
It's been a while, Sir.

719
00:54:30,251 --> 00:54:32,622
I heard reporters at Hyunsung Daily

720
00:54:32,622 --> 00:54:36,761
got their hands on some confidential documents at our research institute.

721
00:54:36,761 --> 00:54:39,462
Hando Steel, Ahjin Motors.

722
00:54:39,462 --> 00:54:40,602
   

723
00:54:40,602 --> 00:54:42,802
What do you mean, Sir?

724
00:54:42,802 --> 00:54:47,042
Everyone is saying Chang Je was ordered by Soonyang

725
00:54:47,042 --> 00:54:50,011
to deliberately launch the investigation.

726
00:54:50,011 --> 00:54:53,682
I heard it'd be on the front page of the newspapers tomorrow morning.

727
00:54:53,682 --> 00:54:56,912
Once the article is published,

728
00:54:56,912 --> 00:55:00,312
all the voters will turn away from the ruling party.

729
00:55:01,681 --> 00:55:04,021
- Lower your voice, honey. 
 - Then just go home!

730
00:55:04,021 --> 00:55:05,691
Honey, this isn't a good idea...

731
00:55:05,691 --> 00:55:08,161
- I told you not to follow me! 
 - Okay, all right. Slow down.

732
00:55:08,161 --> 00:55:09,362
Have you no pride?

733
00:55:09,362 --> 00:55:10,992
- It's just that... 
 - Be quiet!

734
00:55:10,992 --> 00:55:12,861
Please, honey. It's nothing...

735
00:55:12,861 --> 00:55:15,162
Be quiet! Just go home!

736
00:55:15,162 --> 00:55:16,832
Gosh, honey. Wait.

737
00:55:16,832 --> 00:55:19,241
- I told you not to follow me! 
 - Honey, but still...

738
00:55:19,241 --> 00:55:21,072
- Does this even make sense? 
 - Calm down.

739
00:55:21,072 --> 00:55:25,111
What kind of father ruins his own children's future?

740
00:55:25,111 --> 00:55:26,881
Some fathers do. Don't cry.

741
00:55:26,881 --> 00:55:29,551
My dear Hwa Young, don't cry. My sweet Hwa Young.

742
00:55:29,551 --> 00:55:32,381
All right, that's enough. This will only stir things up.

743
00:55:32,381 --> 00:55:33,582
Let's go. Come on.

744
00:55:33,582 --> 00:55:34,881
- Let's go home. 
 - Honey, let go.

745
00:55:34,881 --> 00:55:35,852
What? Okay, look.

746
00:55:35,852 --> 00:55:38,191
I must talk to Father and settle this matter once and for all.

747
00:55:38,191 --> 00:55:40,861
Honey, calm down. You're too worked up right now.

748
00:55:40,861 --> 00:55:43,162
What are you doing here?

749
00:55:43,162 --> 00:55:45,931
Honey, it's Do Jun. It's okay.

750
00:55:45,931 --> 00:55:51,132
If you're here to see Grandpa, Uncle Chang Je should go upstairs alone.

751
00:55:51,132 --> 00:55:55,142
- What did you say? 
 - Must you be like this, too?

752
00:55:55,142 --> 00:56:00,742
If Auntie Hwa Young tagged along, Grandpa would just see you as his son-in-law.

753
00:56:00,742 --> 00:56:03,741
Not as a mayoral candidate.

754
00:56:03,741 --> 00:56:06,512
My son-in-law Chang Je, you're here.

755
00:56:06,512 --> 00:56:09,281
   

756
00:56:09,281 --> 00:56:11,822
Are you done having fun?

757
00:56:17,392 --> 00:56:20,931
Once the article comes out tomorrow morning,

758
00:56:22,301 --> 00:56:28,831
you'll have to stop pretending to be a righteous prosecutor.

759
00:56:29,671 --> 00:56:32,842
Don't take it to heart, though.

760
00:56:32,842 --> 00:56:38,112
I'll open a law firm for you now that you've left the prosecution.

761
00:56:39,251 --> 00:56:42,222
You're right, Father.

762
00:56:42,222 --> 00:56:46,151
I should stop pretending to be a righteous prosecutor.

763
00:56:47,392 --> 00:56:51,461
I plan to do it properly from now on.

764
00:56:53,231 --> 00:56:56,932
I'll be a hunter who goes after the conglomerates.

765
00:57:00,972 --> 00:57:03,672
About Soonyang Life Science, Father,

766
00:57:03,672 --> 00:57:07,671
the real reason they liquidated all the assets in the midst of the "Big Deal" negotiations.

767
00:57:07,671 --> 00:57:10,412
